summary: SummaryThe MAC Strobe Highlighting Moisturizer Cream is a two-in-one moisturizer and highlighter that boosts the look of dull skin and illuminates with iridescent particles.

reviews.headline: All I can say is WOW
reviews.comments: I was not even aware of this product until recently (I don't gravitate toward Mac a lot), but when I saw the new purple shade I just had to try this.  I am applying this right before my foundation and it preps my skin so nicely.  Yes, it gives some glow, but it is not overwhelming, nor does it emphasize my textures.  My makeup looks amazing with this underneath. Recommend!

reviews.headline: Worth it!

reviews.headline: GET.IT.RIGHT.NOW.
reviews.comments: I love this Mac so much! My mum gave me this today, because she does not use it as much anymore, and I'm OBSESSED!! It moisturizes so well, and it gives me the perfect glowy look. MAC, I love you soo much!

reviews.headline: One of my favorite highlighting products
reviews.comments: This produces a beautiful glow with a moisturizing finish that helps keep dynamic areas moisturized, thus minimizing the appearance of fine lines. I have a travel size bottle that I keep in my makeup bag if I am traveling away from home for periods of time as it holds up better than powders due in a bag. It's so easy to dab some on with my other minimal makeup products (concealer, brows, mascara, this product) to freshen up my appearance on the fly. Its truly a your skin but better makeup product as its not overly shimmery or glittery. I admit, I have a few different highlighters (one of my favorite makeup steps) that I alternate through, but this is one I will always continue to buy. The creaminess is especially good for the winter months when things get dry. I have the pink one, and it doesn't noticeably lean to any particular shade on my warm-fair skin, it just looks like glowy, healthy skin.

reviews.headline: Go to product!
reviews.comments: I wore this out and literally was asked multiple times if I had gotten a facial that day. The gold pearl mosturizer is THAT GIRL!

reviews.headline: I absolutely love it on no makeup days
reviews.comments: I tried the tested over a month ago and loved the glow it gave on the back of my hand, so finally purchased it and so happy I did. I got the gold one, and I like to use this on days I don't want to do a lot of makeup so I use this in place of foundation or skin tint. It makes me have a beautiful glow and doesn't make me feel greasy.

reviews.headline: Perfect Pearlescent Pink
reviews.comments: I love this stuff! As someone who with sensitive, flaky skin, i cant always wear foundation. Instead, ill use this as an illuminating base and spot conceal as needed. This technique gives you a your skin but better look and makes your skin look like its glowing from within! Id definitely recommend to all skin types, as i am oily and still thoroughly enjoy this product!

reviews.headline: Yes I will purchase this product again
reviews.comments: Very & light creamy to use as primer or foundation

reviews.headline: Love, Love, LOVE
reviews.comments: From the words of my MAC sales associate in ULTA, "it's a crime not to prime." And boy was he right! I had no idea my skin would feel so much better with makeup on (and even before I put the makeup on) when I used this strobe cream. It leaves your face almost glowing after application and isn't too thick or dense on my face. In fact, my skin actually feels extremely hydrated and amazing after applying this cream!

reviews.headline: Love to shine - In Pink
reviews.comments: I really do love this cream. I put it on under my foundation and in some cases just this and some powder. It adds a nice little glow with a hint of pink. I will even wear it alone or with some sunscreen. You can never go wrong with this one in any of its tints!

reviews.headline: Why this type of scent???
reviews.comments: Gorgeous product but why else is no one talking about the scent? I can't use it because its too overwhelming and thats coming from someone who actually favors/is fine with scented products as long as they're appealing. This straight up smells like pungent laundry detergent and parsley. Everytime I use it I gotta hold my breath or else I feel nauseous so at this point its gonna have to be a return sadly.

reviews.headline: So many compliments!
reviews.comments: I frequently receive compliments on my glowing skin when using this. I use the golden glow color way and absolutely love the texture and the glowy payoff. Its not glittery or shimmery- just radiant. I use the chanel liquid highlighters and personally I think this is better!

reviews.headline: Moisturize and nice glow
reviews.comments: I tried other brand but it was way too much. This MAC Strobe Cream is just right. I can see the difference with and without. When I don't wear makeup, I still use it to make my face little bright and glow. Perfect!

reviews.headline: I will forever buy this product!
reviews.comments: Love this stuff!

reviews.headline: favorite liquid illuminator
reviews.comments: i love this product so much. i either apply it over primer before foundation or i mix it in to thin out the coverage for a tinted moisturizer. i like this better than some other liquid highlighting products like milani soft focus glow or elf halo because of how natural the glow is. strobe cream has a very subtle pearlescent to it. the others can give off a more dewy/illuminated look which just makes me look oilier as the day goes on. strobe cream gives a very healthy look to the skin. like you drink a lot of water and are moisturized well. i like goldlite for my skin tone.

faceoff_positive.comments: Idk if anybody realized this but you can buy the travel size that has 1 oz in it for $12. this has 1.7 oz for $33 so you could buy 2 of the $12 ones and get 3 oz more for about $10 less.... I liked this product a lot and will be buying the travel size again lol!
faceoff_positive.headline: Liked this but...

faceoff_negative.comments: PLEASE change the packaging!! I love this moisturizer and the natural looking glow that it gives my face, but the bottle is terrible! It is too rigid and when the product gets low, it is very hard to get out. I feel like a lot is being left behind. I cut the bottle open to get to it and stored in in a plastic bag so it wouldn't dry, but I really don't care to go through that trouble again. I see many of your primers and other skin products use this packaging... until it changes, I will not try these either! Such a shame because I absolutely LOVE MAC Cosmetics!!
faceoff_negative.headline: WONDERFUL product, best of it's kind! BUT terrible bottle!
